hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Equilibrium condition $dU/dR|_{R_0}=0$ gives
$$\frac{dU}{dR}=-\frac{A}{\rho}e^{-R/\rho}+\frac{M}{R^2}+\frac{6C}{R^7}=0
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac{A\,e^{-R_0/\rho}}{\rho}=\frac{M}{R_0^2}+\frac{6C}{R_0^7}.$$

2. Second derivative at equilibrium,
$$\frac{d^2U}{dR^2}
=\frac{A}{\rho^2}e^{-R/\rho}-\frac{2M}{R^3}-\frac{42C}{R^8},$$
and the bulk modulus relation
$$B_0=\frac{1}{18R_0}\Bigl.\frac{d^2U}{dR^2}\Bigr|_{R_0}$$
yields
$$\frac{A\,e^{-R_0/\rho}}{\rho^2}
=18R_0B_0+\frac{2M}{R_0^3}+\frac{42C}{R_0^8}.$$

3. Dividing the second result by the first,
$$\frac{1}{\rho}
=\frac{18R_0B_0+\tfrac{2M}{R_0^3}+\tfrac{42C}{R_0^8}}
{\tfrac{M}{R_0^2}+\tfrac{6C}{R_0^7}}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\rho
=\frac{\tfrac{M}{R_0^2}+\tfrac{6C}{R_0^7}}
{18R_0B_0+\tfrac{2M}{R_0^3}+\tfrac{42C}{R_0^8}}.$$
